31namespace webrtc {
32
33namespace {
34class ObjCVideoDecoder : public VideoDecoder {
35 public:
36 ObjCVideoDecoder(id<RTCVideoDecoder> decoder)
37 : decoder_(decoder), implementation_name_([decoder implementationName].stdString) {}
38
39 int32_t InitDecode(const VideoCodec *codec_settings, int32_t number_of_cores) override {
40 return [decoder_ startDecodeWithNumberOfCores:number_of_cores];
41 }
42
43 int32_t Decode(const EncodedImage &input_image,
44 bool missing_frames,
45 int64_t render_time_ms = -1) override {
46 RTCEncodedImage *encodedImage =
47 [[RTCEncodedImage alloc] initWithNativeEncodedImage:input_image];
48
49 return [decoder_ decode:encodedImage
50 missingFrames:missing_frames
51 codecSpecificInfo:nil
52 renderTimeMs:render_time_ms];
53 }
54
55 int32_t RegisterDecodeCompleteCallback(DecodedImageCallback *callback) override {
56 [decoder_ setCallback:^(RTCVideoFrame *frame) {
57 const rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoFrameBuffer> buffer =
58 new rtc::RefCountedObject<ObjCFrameBuffer>(frame.buffer);
59 VideoFrame videoFrame =
60 VideoFrame::Builder()
61 .set_video_frame_buffer(buffer)
62 .set_timestamp_rtp((uint32_t)(frame.timeStampNs / rtc::kNumNanosecsPerMicrosec))
63 .set_timestamp_ms(0)
64 .set_rotation((VideoRotation)frame.rotation)
65 .build();
66 videoFrame.set_timestamp(frame.timeStamp);
67
68 callback->Decoded(videoFrame);
69 }];
70
71 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
72 }
73
74 int32_t Release() override { return [decoder_ releaseDecoder]; }
75
76 const char *ImplementationName() const override { return implementation_name_.c_str(); }
77
78 private:
79 id<RTCVideoDecoder> decoder_;
80 const std::string implementation_name_;
81};
82} // namespace
83
84ObjCVideoDecoderFactory::ObjCVideoDecoderFactory(id<RTCVideoDecoderFactory> decoder_factory)
85 : decoder_factory_(decoder_factory) {}
86
87ObjCVideoDecoderFactory::~ObjCVideoDecoderFactory() {}
88
89id<RTCVideoDecoderFactory> ObjCVideoDecoderFactory::wrapped_decoder_factory() const {
90 return decoder_factory_;
91}
92
93std::unique_ptr<VideoDecoder> ObjCVideoDecoderFactory::CreateVideoDecoder(
94 const SdpVideoFormat &format) {
95 NSString *codecName = [NSString stringWithUTF8String:format.name.c_str()];
96 for (RTCVideoCodecInfo *codecInfo in decoder_factory_.supportedCodecs) {
97 if ([codecName isEqualToString:codecInfo.name]) {
98 id<RTCVideoDecoder> decoder = [decoder_factory_ createDecoder:codecInfo];
99
100 // Because of symbol conflict, isKindOfClass doesn't work as expected.
101 // See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=198782.
102 // if ([decoder isKindOfClass:[RTCWrappedNativeVideoDecoder class]]) {
103#if !defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
104 if ([codecName isEqual:@"VP8"] || [codecName isEqual:@"VP9"]) {
105#else
106 if (![decoder.implementationName isEqual:@"VideoToolbox"]) {
107#endif
108 return [(RTCWrappedNativeVideoDecoder *)decoder releaseWrappedDecoder];
109 } else {
110 return std::unique_ptr<ObjCVideoDecoder>(new ObjCVideoDecoder(decoder));
111 }
112 }
113 }
114
115 return nullptr;
116}
117
118std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> ObjCVideoDecoderFactory::GetSupportedFormats() const {
119 std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> supported_formats;
120 for (RTCVideoCodecInfo *supportedCodec in decoder_factory_.supportedCodecs) {
121 SdpVideoFormat format = [supportedCodec nativeSdpVideoFormat];
122 supported_formats.push_back(format);
123 }
124
125 return supported_formats;
126}
